Covid information for the Jv Football At August 31 6:00 in Ravenna
Information from Ravenna Public Schools

1.) Mask will be required to gain entry into the game and must remain on while in the building. We will have disposable masks for sale at the gate if someone needs one to get in.
2.) We ask the Amherst fans to sit on the south side of the field and maintain proper social distance if not in the same family. Ravenna fans will sit on the north side of the field.
3.) If parents are going to feed the team after the game we ask that it be a grab and go type item they can give them as they get on the bus. This way we can avoid gathering in the school area.

Admission: All tickets $3.00

post_text:
PHYSICALS FOR THE 2020-2021 SCHOOL YEAR
Reminder new students, incoming 7th graders and incoming 9th graders are required to have a physical.

Sports physicals on file for the 2019-2020 school year for incoming 8th and 10th-12th grade students will be valid for the 2020-2021 school year.

All incoming freshmen are still required to get a sports physical.

All incoming 7th graders need to get a physical before the start of 7th grade. This is a Nebraska state education law.

These need to be completed before the first day of volleyball, football and cross country practices. Students must have this completed before they are allowed to participate in NSAA sanctioned sports/activities.

post_text:
Elementary Students will check out next week. PK-6th grade will return items on May 18, 19 and 20th. Times will be from 9 AM - 6 PM on Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday. Students should return IPad, charger, textbooks, library books, etc. Please keep each student’s items separated. Also, disinfect all items before you return them. All items should be dropped off at the entryway in the parking lot on the north side of the building.

If you are unsure what items you should return please communicate with your teacher. Teachers will contact students on Thursday the 21st if you are missing something.

post_text:
Dear Bookmobile patrons,

We hope you are all safe and healthy. Know that we are missing you.

At this point it does not seem likely that Bookmobile services will resume until June at the earliest. In the meantime we would like to work with you to get library materials returned to the Kearney Public Library at your earliest convenience.
First, we ask that you collect as many KPL books as possible and box them up.
Second, please bring them to the large garage door on the West side of the library. This is where the Bookmobile lives at the library.
Call 233-3287 (Bookmobile office) or 233-3283 (my office) to schedule a time so we can open the doors to unload your returns.
We are at the library from 8-5 Monday through Thursday for the time being.
If this is not workable please call me and we will seek an alternative plan to return materials to the library.

Thank you for your patience and we look forward to seeing you down the road.

post_text:
Amherst Academic Decathlon is going to State!
On January 18th, the team of 6 scored enough points to earn Runner up for Very Small schools and Rookie of the Year. Testing at the Honors A level was Riley Adelung and Michael Klingelhoefer. At the Scholastic B level was Hayden Adam and Wesley Christiansen. At the Varsity C level was Cheyenne Leo and Ashley Wempen. Total they earned 9 gold medals, 4 silver medals and 6 bronze medals. Studying about Health Care they tested on six different subjects.They then competed as a team in a SuperQuiz earning bronze.
Supporting them as an alternate team was Jon Christensen and Erin Murphy on the Honors team and Tanner Thomsen on the alternate Scholastic team. Total they earned 1 gold, 2 silvers, and 8 bronze medals.
Very proud of this rookie team. Congratulate them and wish them luck on Feb. 21 and 22. They will travel to Omaha and take 6 more quizzes, one more SuperQuiz, give an impromptu speech, a prepared speech, and participate in an interview.
